$ SQL: where

Special precaution needs to be taken when using a `where` condition with the `=` or `<>` operator on an
→ development/databases/SQL/data-types/predefined/numeric/approximate[approximate numeric data type] is performed.

sa:
  Much as the SQL `where` clause is used to specify on which records an SQL operation is peformed, the → Windows/PowerShell/command-inventory/noun/object/select[`select-object cmdLet`] is used to specify which
  PowerShell-objects are kept in a → Windows/PowerShell/pipeline[PowerShell pipeline].

  In → Microsoft/Office/Excel, a worksheet's → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/AutoFilter[`autoFilter`] object allows to filter rows based on the values of its cells.
  -
  The → Microsoft/Office/Excel/functions/filter[worksheet function `filter`] also allows to select poritions of a → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Range[range] that match a certain criteria.

